\par    }{\b\fs28 4. B. azorica}{\fs28  Hochst. in Seub., }{\i\fs28 Fl. Azor.}{\fs28  31 (1844). Like }{\b\fs28 2 }{\fs28 but with decumbent to ascending, leafy stems up to 15 cm; capitula not more than 13 mm in diameter; receptacle nearly flat, irregularly tuberculate between the florets; involucral bracts 3-4 mm, acute or obtuse; ligules 5-6 mm, not more than 1\'bd times as long as bracts; achenes subglabrous, but with numerous subsessile glands.}{\i\fs28  Mountain pastures. \bullet  A\'e7ores.}{\fs28  Az.
