\par    }{\b\fs28 2. B. minutum}{\fs28  (L.) L., }{\i\fs28 op. cit.}{\fs28  286 (1771). Sparsely pubescent, scapose annual. Leaves 5-8 \'d7 3-5 mm, elliptic-obovate; petiole about as long as the lamina. Peduncles 2-5 cm, very slender, numerous. Capitula 6-7 mm in diameter, with 7-10 involucral bracts and ligules. Involucral bracts 2-2\'b75 mm, elliptic-oblong, acute. Ligules scarcely exceeding the bracts.}{\i\fs28  Maritime rocks. Mediterranean islands, westwards to Lampedusa; very local.}{\fs28  Cr Gr Si.
\par 
\par    }{\b\fs28 3. B. crassifolium}{\fs28  Moris, }{\i\fs28 Stirp. Sard.}{\b\fs28  1}{\fs28 : 26 (1827). Perennial. Stem 0-10 cm, rather woody, decumbent to suberect, sparingly branched. Leaves 9-15 mm, alternate or subverticillate, orbicular to elliptic-spathulate, fleshy, glabrous or pubescent; petiole 15-40 mm. Capitula 15-20 mm in diameter, terminal or pseudoterminal, usually with 20-30 involucral bracts and ligules. Peduncles 5-18 cm, stout. Involucral bracts 5-6 mm, subacute. Ligules 4-6 mm.}{\i\fs28  Maritime rocks. Sardegna.}{\fs28  Sa.
